Package org.neo4j.internal.recordstorage

Interface TransactionApplier

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, CommandVisitor, Visitor<StorageCommand,​IOException>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CacheInvalidationTransactionApplier, ConsistencyCheckingApplierFactory.ConsistencyCheckingApplier, CountsStoreTransactionApplier, HighIdTransactionApplier, IndexTransactionApplierFactory.SingleTransactionApplier, NeoStoreTransactionApplier, PropertyCommandsExtractor, TransactionApplier.Adapter, TransactionApplierFacade
    public interface TransactionApplier
extends Visitor<StorageCommand,​IOException>, CommandVisitor, AutoCloseable
    Responsible for a single transaction. See also TransactionApplierFactory which returns an implementation of this class. Should typically be used in a try-with-resources block, f.ex.: 
     
     try ( TransactionApplier txApplier = batchTxApplier.startTx( txToApply )
     {
         // Apply the transaction
         txToApply.transactionRepresentation().accept( txApplier );
         // Or apply other commands
         // txApplier.visit( command );
     }

      Delegates to individual visit methods (see CommandVisitor) which need to be implemented, as well as TransactionApplier.Adapter.close() if applicable.
